 FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>4/15/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>8:13:06 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My thoughts...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">From Arris...<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hail to my fellow brethren of the sword and faith. I come to you today with a heavy heart. I wish not accuse anyone of anything, nor am I arrogant to assume that I could ever describe the role or place of paladinhood in the land of Norrath. I am truly speaking from my heart and just wish for a few of my brothers and sisters in arms to listen to me.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I have seen many brave and great deeds, along with the most foul of treachary and betrayl. I have been witness to the gravest of injustices (that were, unfortunatly, out of my control). I am in the 20th season on the Lanys T'Vyl server. Some say that is really a long time, most say I am still too young to truly understand my gift of Knighthood.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp My life so far here has been nothing but an endless procession of deaths, struggles, injustice, and just plain outright hard times. I have seen most of my friends level past me, truly realizing that the next time I group with them won't be untill were are all in our 40's. With the expection of Holy swords and the like, you will not see numbers comparable to that of a warrior in terms of outright melee damage. Our magic will never be that of a cleric's superiority. I have wondered why I see the Shadow Knight's Dark Reaver or the warrior's Executioner's Axe, most of the non-planar ultimate armor (i.e. Lambent, Ravenscale, etc..), and other class's items daily on the auction block, but never once have i seen a piece of Ro, Ghoulbane, or even a Deepwater Harpoon auctioned. I have heard of these sold very rarely, and even then, it has almost never been a paladin making the auction. Our quests are arguably longer, harder, more invloved, complex and result in almost nothing more than what other classes can obtain with a few hundred or thousand platinum at your local bazaar. Make no mistake, I don't believe they should be there, but it upsets me a little that I could easily purchase a Dark Reaver, if choose to do so.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp And the answer to my questions are: because I choose paladinhood. It is a very simple answer, although the meaning behind it is so complex, each of us must determine what it means to be a paladin. Is it worth it? Is it what you want? Most people who i have asked have said no, by a far majority. Yet there are those who truly spark my imagination, people who truly belive it is worth it. Some say our class is nothing more than a flaming sword with some poor stats. Some say that our place in a group is a liability. And there are a few of of us who truly understand.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I have been questioned by many why I choose paladin as my class, and have never been really able to answer them. Well, the reason I write this is because I have found out what paladinhood means to me..I finally know why all this time and effort is worth it to me. It is who I am. And I suspect that is that might be very similar to the reason of many other who have committed themselves to the class I speak of, even if they do not know it for themselves.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It is in our hearts and minds that we truly know what we are for. When we do finally achieve our armor of Ro after months of dead ends and truly horrific questing, when we do finally have he proud honor of wielding SoulFire, paladins are only reminded of what they stand for. We are not defined by are stats, magic, or any other factor other than what we do, say, and think. Nor am I saying we are weak, I have seen a paladin out-duel two warriors at once (by the very skin of his teeth, mind you) of an equal level (50). We know how to fight, and when it comes to it, we can defend ourselves and still stand for more even after the most vicious and brutal of battles.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I am not trying to say that any other class is weaker in thier own right. We are all, for the most part on equal terms, contrary to the claims of most people. What I'm saying is that we are the only class, in my opinion, that is truely defined by what we do. We live or die by our skill and intelligince, not just our stats. Our honor is not measured by the damage we inflict, nor what wealth we can amass...it is defined by who we are.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I may be crazy, or I may not even know what I am talking about. Inevitably, some will say what I have wrote is a &quot;flame&quot; against all other classes, or that I think paladins are better than others. I truly think that we are all equal, and that what I expressed here is what I feel is my own defining explination of a paladin...not anyone else's. Please do not take this as an insult if you are not a paladin, nor do not take it as what a paladin should be if you are. I am just hoping to inspire the thoughts of my brothers and sisters in arms to think long and hard about the choices they once made and what whatever other choices they may make in the future.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I am sorry if this seems to be a rant or a flame or anything of the like, I truly apologize if it seems that way. These are just a few of my thoughts, and I hope to share many more someday (If i get a positive reponse here, I have many more files I have written like this that I could share here =).<br>
<br>
Arris<br>
Of the Lanys T'Vyl server</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uranadorbrightblade.showPublicProfile>Ranador Brightblade</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>4/15/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>8:52:21 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Paladins of Norrath</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Greetings brother Arris!<br>
<br>
Yours is a profound and thought provoking statement. I, too, considered long and hard about choosing the path of a paladin. I tried the ways of magic as a wizard but found it to be unfulfilling. My brother plays as a Dwarven Warrior and I have watched him many times and found very little thought involved in the ways of the warrior.<br>
<br>
I agree with your statement that, to an extent, all classes are equal. There are strengths and weaknesses to all classes. At times, it even seems that some classes have certain advantages over others.<br>
<br>
I am only an 11th season paladin but it has taken me many months to achieve this. In that time I have seen many of my friends that started after me far surpass my level and, perhaps, take the easy way to achieve that success. Sometimes, being a paladin means having to sacrifice your own needs and desires in favor of helping others to achieve their greater good.<br>
<br>
I believe that one who truly seeks the way of the paladin can see and understand that, as you said, we are not defined by our stats or posessions but by our actions. I do not say this to belittle or put down other classes and say that there are not other classes who pursue more than posessions. On the contrary, I have encountered other classes who have exhibited the qualities of a paladin far better than I. What I am saying is that for the paladin, it is a way of life. To consider others as better than ourselves, to stand up for what is good and true, to even sacrifice ourselves for the greater good is not something that everyone can do. If, in that pursuit, we are able to attain strength or posessions, than that is a gift from Marr. But when it becomes greater than seeking the truth and upholding all that is good, then one must rethink why they have chosen to be a paladin.<br>
<br>
It is a choice that everyone must put serious consideration into and make for themselves. Simply because one decides not to be a paladin does not make them any less or better than any other class. But when one decides to become a paladin, it is a choice that will require much effort and perserverance. And one will be judged by how they act as a paladin. You may not gain the physical things as quickly as others, but the spiritual rewards will be much greater!<br>
<br>
May Mithaniel Marr guide you in all that you do!<br>
<br>
Ranador<br>
11th season Paladin<br>
Prexus<br>
