and be effective. At 30 my friend who I was ahead of in my teens have surpassed me, some are nearly lvl 40 and I am still working on 30. My guild has shuned many of my friends and now they are gone, and I often feel alone as no one is brave enough it seems to come with me on my quests, after all there is no profit in it for them. Often times I am forced to go it alone, and at lvl 30 being alone is a nightmare. So you can see, it does not get any easier.<br>
<br>
However this is what I always remind myself of. This is what I have choosen. All and all this has been my dream since I was a boy, a chance to be a Knight. (being an elf is kind of cool too =) )   In real life, wearing armor wielding swords and the like would probably get me thrown in jail. Chivalry is often rewarded with strange looks and giggles (though this is not always so). So it is with Everquest that I am able to do this. So here it is. I knew when I choose this it would not be easy. Besides if it were easy the reward would mean very little. It takes a very special person to succeed with a Paladin and they are out there. Beld, Romidar, Varrus, Bephsi and so many others have proven this. It is a difficult life to lead and not everyone can do it. I will also tell you that it seems like for every level you gain, your friends gain 2 or 3. <br>
<br>
Let me tell you I miss my friends. So we are all faced with a choice here. We can either give up, or we can do what most people can not and BE a Paladin. Have the courage to push on even when it seems like the task is impossible.<br>
